      "Crew members reported incident to Cox Operating PIC onboard"
    ],
    "summary": "On 24 January 2020 at 1900 hours, a section of concrete stairway (5 ft 6 in X 4 ft 9 in) fell 30 feet into the Gulf of Mexico during construction work to replace corroded handrails, stairways and deck grating at WD 30-P platform. The stairway broke loose during the third cut of a welding/cutting operation. The incident was not reported by Cox Operating LLC until 31 January 2020, seven days after occurrence. Investigation revealed multiple failures including inadequate securing of the stairway, failure to use Stop Work Authority, and improper rigging procedures.",
